  "title": "FP&A Analyst",
  "description": "<p><strong>Overview:</strong><br />This role manages finances across APAC, supports month‑end closing, forecasting, budgeting, and provides financial insights to leadership, P&L reporting and ad‑hoc analysis.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead monthly closing, budgeting and quarterly forecasts with clear variance explanations.</li><li>Use planning and reporting systems to build forecasts and analyze trends.</li><li>Partner with internal teams to manage cost projections.</li><li>Review actuals vs. forecasts to highlight variances and cost‑saving opportunities.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Finance or Accounting.</li><li>2-3 years of FP&A or related finance experience.</li><li>Strong communication and cross‑functional collaboration skills.</li><li>Skilled in BI dashboard creation (Power BI/Tableau).</li></ul>",
